name: Python: 5 microservice cascading renames — 40 files, 116 hunks
description: 5 microservice packages with cascading heterogeneous renames across 5 layers: (1) shared/types.py renames ServiceRequest->ServicePayload and ServiceResponse->ServiceResult. (2) shared/errors.py renames ServiceError->ServiceFailure, AuthError->AuthFailure, ValidationError->PayloadError. (3) Each service renames its own function AND its request model class. (4) Cross-service clients use BOTH the service's renamed function AND its renamed model. (5) Gateway/router aggregates all renamed functions. (6) Middleware uses auth+user renamed functions + renamed errors. ALL 38 files with renames must be in a single commit. The LLM is tempted to split by layer (shared, services, clients, gateway, middleware) or by service (auth, user, billing, order, notification) — both break cascading deps.
